tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE WindTurbine (
    turbine_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    turbine_name VARCHAR(255),
    location VARCHAR(255),
    rated_capacity FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE TurbineData (
    data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    turbine_id INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    wind_speed FLOAT,
    power_generated FLOAT,
    efficiency FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (turbine_id) REFERENCES WindTurbine(turbine_id)
)

CREATE TABLE MaintenanceLog (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    turbine_id INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    maintenance_type VARCHAR(255),
    maintenance_details TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (turbine_id) REFERENCES WindTurbine(turbine_id)
)

CREATE TABLE WindTurbine (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    turbine_name VARCHAR(255),
    location VARCHAR(255),
    last_maintenance_date DATE,
    power_output DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE WindTurbineData (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    turbine_name VARCHAR(255),
    location VARCHAR(255),
    wind_speed FLOAT,
    power_output FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE MaintenanceRecords (
    record_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    turbine_id INT,
    maintenance_date DATE,
    maintenance_type VARCHAR(255),
    notes TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE WeatherData (
    data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    location VARCHAR(255),
    date DATE,
    temperature FLOAT,
    wind_speed FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE TurbineHealth (
    health_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    turbine_id INT,
    health_status VARCHAR(255),
    last_checkup DATE,
    next_checkup DATE
)

CREATE TABLE TurbineLocations (
    location_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    location_name VARCHAR(255),
    region VARCHAR(255),
    country VARCHAR(255)
)
